WEBVTT

00:00:03.608 --> 00:00:04.818
[Takao] Nakamura...

00:00:04.901 --> 00:00:06.695
Do you remember me?

00:00:08.488 --> 00:00:09.823
It's me, Kasuga.

00:00:10.699 --> 00:00:11.992
Takao Kasuga.

00:00:13.910 --> 00:00:15.579
I came to see you.

00:00:16.121 --> 00:00:17.706
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

00:00:32.429 --> 00:00:33.889
What's that face for?

00:00:36.767 --> 00:00:38.143
Long time no see.

00:00:39.603 --> 00:00:41.063
Long time no see...

00:00:43.732 --> 00:00:45.484
What are you standing there for?

00:00:46.068 --> 00:00:48.737
Go ahead and eat. It's good.

00:00:53.450 --> 00:00:54.451
Uh...

00:00:55.285 --> 00:00:56.536
[Shino] So...

00:00:57.454 --> 00:00:58.580
You're Kasuga.

00:00:59.790 --> 00:01:01.625
Thanks for coming all this way.

00:01:03.168 --> 00:01:04.544
I'm Sawa's mother.

00:01:09.758 --> 00:01:11.176
I'm sorry, but,

00:01:13.011 --> 00:01:14.513
I want you...

00:01:15.639 --> 00:01:17.349
to leave Sawa alone.

00:01:20.894 --> 00:01:22.270
She's finally...

00:01:23.271 --> 00:01:25.065
found peace with things.

00:01:26.692 --> 00:01:28.402
It's just her and me now.

00:01:34.074 --> 00:01:35.283
I hope you can understand.

00:01:37.828 --> 00:01:38.870
Of course.

00:01:50.132 --> 00:01:51.299
Sawa!

00:01:52.134 --> 00:01:55.095
Kasuga told me about you,
and I came all this way

00:01:55.178 --> 00:01:57.472
because I wanted to meet you!

00:01:57.556 --> 00:02:01.268
I don't know how you feel about Kasuga,

00:02:01.351 --> 00:02:03.979
or it all might not matter to you anymore,

00:02:04.896 --> 00:02:07.899
but can we talk outside for a bit?

00:02:07.983 --> 00:02:09.901
I'm so sorry to bother you like this!

00:02:11.194 --> 00:02:12.404
[Takao] Tokiwa...

00:02:17.409 --> 00:02:18.660
Sure.

00:02:19.870 --> 00:02:22.164
But first, eat.

00:02:22.664 --> 00:02:24.082
Then, we'll talk.

00:02:25.167 --> 00:02:27.002
[♪ gripping music playing]

00:02:28.086 --> 00:02:30.172
[♪ opening theme music playing]

00:03:25.810 --> 00:03:28.063
THE FLOWERS OF EVIL

00:03:32.025 --> 00:03:35.362
FINAL EPISODE

00:03:37.239 --> 00:03:38.865
[Aya] Kasuga,

00:03:39.533 --> 00:03:41.660
don't leave anything half-done, okay?

00:03:42.702 --> 00:03:45.872
That's what I hate the most.

00:03:47.374 --> 00:03:48.458
[Takao] Okay.

00:03:51.670 --> 00:03:53.505
Make sure you don't regret it later.

00:03:55.131 --> 00:03:56.132
[Takao] All right.

00:04:05.141 --> 00:04:06.518
Nakamura.
STYLE
::cue()

00:04:12.566 --> 00:04:13.733
So...

00:04:14.818 --> 00:04:17.153
you live with your mother now?

00:04:17.779 --> 00:04:19.406
[Sawa] That's right.

00:04:22.909 --> 00:04:24.661
What happened to your dad?

00:04:27.539 --> 00:04:29.249
Nakamura...

00:04:30.625 --> 00:04:31.793
Since that day,

00:04:33.962 --> 00:04:36.172
how have you been living your life?

00:04:37.299 --> 00:04:38.717
I don't remember.

00:04:39.509 --> 00:04:41.928
It doesn't matter anymore.

00:04:49.561 --> 00:04:50.729
Look.

00:04:53.732 --> 00:04:55.191
[♪ somber music playing]

00:04:55.275 --> 00:04:58.653
In this town, the sun sets into the sea.

00:04:59.779 --> 00:05:01.156
But after a while,

00:05:01.698 --> 00:05:03.825
it comes up from the sea on that side.

00:05:04.492 --> 00:05:06.995
Forever and ever.

00:05:07.579 --> 00:05:09.748
Round and round.

00:05:10.624 --> 00:05:13.084
It's beautiful, isn't it?

00:05:15.879 --> 00:05:17.088
[Takao] I don't know.

00:05:19.424 --> 00:05:21.009
That day,

00:05:22.135 --> 00:05:24.429
on the riverbank
on our way to the summer festival,

00:05:24.512 --> 00:05:26.890
you saw the sunset
and said it was "beautiful."

00:05:29.225 --> 00:05:31.353
Is that sky and this sky

00:05:32.604 --> 00:05:33.688
the same to you?

00:05:35.523 --> 00:05:37.150
[♪ somber music continues]

00:05:40.612 --> 00:05:41.863
Nakamura,

00:05:44.824 --> 00:05:46.534
there's something I want to ask you.

00:05:52.082 --> 00:05:53.166
That night,

00:05:54.668 --> 00:05:56.878
why did you shove me away?

00:06:04.678 --> 00:06:05.845
Who knows?

00:06:07.389 --> 00:06:08.848
I've forgotten.

00:06:34.374 --> 00:06:35.750
Are you...

00:06:35.834 --> 00:06:37.377
dating her?

00:06:38.503 --> 00:06:40.088
That person.

00:06:50.682 --> 00:06:51.975
Yes.

00:06:58.398 --> 00:06:59.441
I see.

00:07:03.111 --> 00:07:04.529
I'm happy for you.

00:07:06.364 --> 00:07:09.451
You chose the same path as everybody.

00:07:11.161 --> 00:07:12.787
What about you, Nakamura?

00:07:18.042 --> 00:07:19.627
[waves crashing]

00:07:25.759 --> 00:07:26.843
[Sawa] Okay, then.

00:07:27.343 --> 00:07:28.928
Good luck.

00:07:34.768 --> 00:07:36.060
Wait!

00:07:40.690 --> 00:07:41.858
Sawa,

00:07:42.358 --> 00:07:43.735
I...

00:07:44.235 --> 00:07:46.738
I don't have anything to do with you, but,

00:07:48.072 --> 00:07:49.115
still...

00:07:53.953 --> 00:07:55.246
it makes me sad.

00:07:56.498 --> 00:07:58.208
Watching you,

00:07:59.417 --> 00:08:00.668
it makes me sad,

00:08:01.377 --> 00:08:02.378
and it's painful.

00:08:03.922 --> 00:08:05.381
It's not sympathy or anything.

00:08:06.174 --> 00:08:07.175
It's because...

00:08:08.259 --> 00:08:10.470
it's as if I'm watching my past self.

00:08:12.847 --> 00:08:13.973
Sawa...

00:08:20.271 --> 00:08:23.441
There's a path for you
to live on with Kasuga.
STYLE
::cue()

00:08:24.984 --> 00:08:26.027
Because...

00:08:26.653 --> 00:08:28.029
the two of you are...

00:08:28.613 --> 00:08:29.948
probably...

00:08:30.031 --> 00:08:31.199
more than anyone else...

00:08:33.701 --> 00:08:34.869
If...

00:08:39.457 --> 00:08:42.043
If the two of you can live together...

00:08:45.255 --> 00:08:46.297
That'd be...

00:08:46.840 --> 00:08:47.841
the best for...

00:08:52.887 --> 00:08:54.305
[sniffles]

00:08:58.017 --> 00:08:59.185
The best for...

00:09:14.284 --> 00:09:16.035
[Takao panting]

00:09:16.536 --> 00:09:18.913
[Takao grunts, yells]

00:09:18.997 --> 00:09:20.081
Kasuga?

00:09:20.999 --> 00:09:23.293
[Takao grunting]

00:09:28.464 --> 00:09:29.465
[Takao yells]

00:09:30.717 --> 00:09:33.928
[Takao grunting loudly, panting]

00:09:41.436 --> 00:09:42.729
Nakamura...

00:09:45.064 --> 00:09:47.317
I can't hold on to anything.

00:09:49.194 --> 00:09:50.570
No matter how much I try.

00:09:52.322 --> 00:09:54.407
Even when I can practically feel it.

00:09:56.367 --> 00:09:58.328
The moment I think I'm there,

00:09:59.204 --> 00:10:00.622
the journey begins again.

00:10:03.875 --> 00:10:04.918
So...

00:10:08.046 --> 00:10:10.506
That's why it still makes me happy...

00:10:13.718 --> 00:10:16.262
to see that you haven't left this world.

00:10:16.346 --> 00:10:18.473
[sobbing]

00:10:28.608 --> 00:10:30.360
[Takao continues sobbing]

00:10:42.121 --> 00:10:43.539
[Takao grunts]

00:10:45.250 --> 00:10:46.668
[Takao grunting]

00:10:47.377 --> 00:10:48.378
[Sawa grunting]

00:10:50.838 --> 00:10:52.090
[Takao yelps]

00:10:54.259 --> 00:10:55.593
[Sawa grunts]

00:10:55.677 --> 00:10:56.678
Kasuga!

00:10:58.721 --> 00:11:00.139
-[Takao grunts]
-[Aya screaming]

00:11:00.223 --> 00:11:02.058
[♪ soft rock music playing]

00:11:03.268 --> 00:11:04.686
[Takao grunting]

00:11:05.979 --> 00:11:07.355
-[Sawa screaming]
-[grunts]

00:11:15.071 --> 00:11:16.906
[panting]

00:11:20.159 --> 00:11:22.203
[Sawa laughing]

00:11:25.540 --> 00:11:26.541
[Takao] What the...

00:11:29.585 --> 00:11:31.713
[♪ music continues]

00:11:31.796 --> 00:11:33.506
[Sawa yelps, laughs]

00:11:36.342 --> 00:11:37.844
[all grunting]

00:11:37.927 --> 00:11:39.345
[all laughing]

00:11:45.727 --> 00:11:47.228
[all continue laughing]

00:12:23.056 --> 00:12:24.265
[♪ music ends]
STYLE
::cue()

00:12:24.349 --> 00:12:25.767
[waves lapping]

00:12:30.772 --> 00:12:32.273
[Sawa] Kasuga...

00:12:34.442 --> 00:12:38.112
Don't you ever come again, boring human.

00:12:47.580 --> 00:12:48.748
Thank you.

00:12:54.170 --> 00:12:55.588
Thank you.

00:12:58.299 --> 00:13:00.093
[♪ melancholy music playing]

00:13:38.297 --> 00:13:41.092
THE CASE OF THE SERIAL KILLER GHOST (TBD)

00:14:16.544 --> 00:14:18.588
A FEW YEARS LATER

00:14:18.671 --> 00:14:22.633
KASUGA

00:14:22.717 --> 00:14:24.177
Here you go.

00:14:24.260 --> 00:14:25.469
[customer] Thank you.

00:14:25.553 --> 00:14:26.679
Thank you, come again.

00:14:27.555 --> 00:14:29.765
-[doorbell chimes]
-Say, Kasuga,

00:14:29.849 --> 00:14:31.767
let's remember to smile, all right?

00:14:32.393 --> 00:14:34.353
Right! Sorry, sir.

00:14:37.023 --> 00:14:38.524
[doorbell chimes]

00:14:39.775 --> 00:14:41.152
Welcome!

00:14:51.746 --> 00:14:52.830
Let's eat.

00:15:01.297 --> 00:15:02.882
[knocking at door]

00:15:05.801 --> 00:15:06.886
[chuckles softly]

00:15:08.638 --> 00:15:09.931
[sighs]

00:15:11.807 --> 00:15:13.100
[sighs wearily]

00:15:13.184 --> 00:15:15.978
It's so hot! I'm gonna melt!

00:15:16.062 --> 00:15:17.480
[laughs]

00:15:17.563 --> 00:15:19.690
Hot, hot, hot!

00:15:19.774 --> 00:15:21.150
[both chuckle]

00:15:21.734 --> 00:15:22.735
[Takao] Here you go.

00:15:22.818 --> 00:15:23.986
[Aya] Thanks.

00:15:25.655 --> 00:15:26.989
[♪ gentle music playing]

00:15:27.573 --> 00:15:28.824
[Aya exclaims]

00:15:31.577 --> 00:15:34.330
Ugh. Expired leftovers
from your job again?
STYLE
::cue()

00:15:34.413 --> 00:15:37.416
Come on, that can't be good for you.

00:15:37.500 --> 00:15:38.584
I know.

00:15:40.628 --> 00:15:41.837
[Aya] Oh...

00:15:43.756 --> 00:15:45.299
What's this notebook for?

00:15:45.967 --> 00:15:47.093
[Takao] That?

00:15:48.094 --> 00:15:50.388
I haven't written anything in it yet.

00:15:50.471 --> 00:15:52.056
Okay...

00:15:53.057 --> 00:15:54.475
And, what's the plan for it?

00:15:55.059 --> 00:15:56.269
I don't know.

00:15:56.352 --> 00:15:57.979
[Aya] Okay.

00:15:58.062 --> 00:16:01.357
You should just start writing, you know.
Whatever comes to mind.

00:16:01.941 --> 00:16:04.902
I don't have your talent, Tokiwa.

00:16:04.986 --> 00:16:06.153
Me?

00:16:06.654 --> 00:16:08.030
I don't have any talent.

00:16:08.114 --> 00:16:11.534
No, I think your
new piece was really good.

00:16:11.909 --> 00:16:13.244
I hope you get that award.

00:16:14.161 --> 00:16:15.162
[chuckles softly]

00:16:16.706 --> 00:16:17.915
I'll poke your eyes out!

00:16:17.999 --> 00:16:19.959
[exclaims] Hey!

00:16:20.042 --> 00:16:22.461
[laughs] What was that weak wail?

00:16:22.545 --> 00:16:23.754
That's not safe, you know.

00:16:23.838 --> 00:16:25.006
Baba's overhead chop!

00:16:25.089 --> 00:16:26.549
Wow, that's old school!

00:16:27.258 --> 00:16:28.676
Boom. [laughs]

00:16:28.759 --> 00:16:30.219
Cut it out already.

00:16:34.598 --> 00:16:39.312
[singing] ♪ Up and down, left and right
Make a circle and... ♪

00:16:40.354 --> 00:16:41.731
[Takao chuckles]

00:16:43.190 --> 00:16:44.317
Hey.

00:16:44.984 --> 00:16:46.569
Can I stay the night?

00:16:48.321 --> 00:16:49.322
Sure.

00:16:55.036 --> 00:16:56.620
[Aya] Hey, Kasuga?

00:16:56.704 --> 00:16:57.747
Yeah?

00:16:58.289 --> 00:16:59.290
What is it?

00:17:05.296 --> 00:17:06.422
Nothing.

00:17:08.215 --> 00:17:09.550
Nevermind.

00:17:11.093 --> 00:17:12.094
Okay.

00:17:18.601 --> 00:17:19.977
Hold me.

00:17:23.647 --> 00:17:24.648
Sure.

00:17:30.112 --> 00:17:31.447
Kasuga.

00:17:32.281 --> 00:17:33.324
Yeah?

00:17:35.826 --> 00:17:37.161
You know how I told you

00:17:38.079 --> 00:17:41.666
I wanted to see the town you were born in?

00:17:41.749 --> 00:17:43.167
Do you remember that?

00:17:44.794 --> 00:17:45.878
Yeah.

00:17:50.007 --> 00:17:51.175
Take me.

00:17:51.676 --> 00:17:52.718
Tomorrow.

00:17:56.138 --> 00:17:58.099
There's nothing there to see.

00:18:04.021 --> 00:18:06.399
You say that because you know the town.

00:18:08.693 --> 00:18:10.861
I don't know a thing about the place.

00:18:13.406 --> 00:18:14.990
You mentioned, some time,

00:18:17.284 --> 00:18:19.704
that the town was surrounded by mountains,

00:18:20.663 --> 00:18:23.791
so you always wanted to go
beyond those mountains.

00:18:25.751 --> 00:18:26.752
But...

00:18:29.630 --> 00:18:31.215
to me...

00:18:32.967 --> 00:18:35.511
your hometown is the other side.
STYLE
::cue()

00:18:40.683 --> 00:18:41.767
[bird calling]

00:18:44.228 --> 00:18:46.021
[♪ sentimental music playing]

00:18:52.737 --> 00:18:54.113
[camera shutter clicks]

00:19:07.084 --> 00:19:08.085
[camera shutter clicks]

00:19:16.218 --> 00:19:17.219
[camera shutter clicks]

00:19:17.303 --> 00:19:18.596
[♪ music continues]

00:19:42.203 --> 00:19:44.205
USED BOOKS AND GALLERY
NEKOMACHI-DO

00:20:25.079 --> 00:20:26.080
[camera shutter clicks]

00:20:30.751 --> 00:20:31.752
[♪ music ends]

00:20:31.836 --> 00:20:32.962
How was it?

00:20:36.006 --> 00:20:39.301
Did it look different to you,
seeing it now?

00:20:40.678 --> 00:20:41.762
I'm not sure...

00:20:43.639 --> 00:20:45.099
It looks the same,

00:20:46.433 --> 00:20:47.768
but, it also feels different.

00:20:50.646 --> 00:20:52.231
[Aya] Think you can write something?

00:20:52.857 --> 00:20:53.858
What?

00:20:56.068 --> 00:20:57.903
I think it must be here.

00:20:58.988 --> 00:21:01.031
The thing only you can write.

00:21:05.828 --> 00:21:07.872
The people born in this town,

00:21:09.331 --> 00:21:11.000
live their lives in this town,

00:21:12.209 --> 00:21:13.961
and then die in this town.
STYLE
::cue()

00:21:16.589 --> 00:21:17.923
But, I...

00:21:20.342 --> 00:21:22.469
I couldn't live on in this town.

00:21:23.262 --> 00:21:24.680
[♪ wistful music playing]

00:21:25.472 --> 00:21:28.684
I couldn't find a life
for Nakamura or Saeki, either.

00:21:30.311 --> 00:21:31.729
I couldn't save anyone.

00:21:33.397 --> 00:21:35.357
I couldn't live a proper life,

00:21:36.734 --> 00:21:39.194
nor could I become a true pervert, either.

00:21:40.362 --> 00:21:42.323
-I just kept running--
-Shut up.

00:21:42.948 --> 00:21:44.074
Shit bug.

00:21:44.742 --> 00:21:45.951
Shut up and write.

00:21:57.421 --> 00:21:59.757
Write about that shitty life.

00:22:01.133 --> 00:22:03.552
Live that shitty life.

00:22:04.887 --> 00:22:09.016
Live out that shitty life
for many years to come.

00:22:10.976 --> 00:22:13.687
What's that face for? [chuckles]

00:22:13.771 --> 00:22:17.024
You don't need to think it's fun.

00:22:17.608 --> 00:22:20.694
Because it'll be fun for me.
[laughs playfully]

00:22:22.363 --> 00:22:24.365
[♪ uplifting music playing]

00:22:24.448 --> 00:22:26.241
[Aya laughing]

00:22:28.744 --> 00:22:30.454
[both laughing]

00:22:34.625 --> 00:22:36.543
[♪ uplifting music continues]

00:22:39.880 --> 00:22:41.674
[both continue laughing]

00:22:44.969 --> 00:22:47.054
[Takao] Well, how about this?

00:22:47.721 --> 00:22:51.266
A dead boy
is reincarnated as a girl, and...

00:22:51.350 --> 00:22:53.394
[♪ closing theme music playing]

00:22:58.691 --> 00:23:00.234
[inaudible]

00:23:23.632 --> 00:23:24.925
MIZUKOSHI DINER

00:23:43.193 --> 00:23:45.988
THE FLOWERS OF EVIL
BAUDELAIRE

00:23:46.071 --> 00:23:47.072
THE FLOWERS OF EVIL
THE END

00:23:47.156 --> 00:23:48.157
Translated by Yuka Kristi